(2)




Neural graphs can theoretically represent the parameters of any neural network taking into account neuron permutation symmetry as the rows and columns of weight matrices correspond to the nodes in the neural graph.
This way, neural graphs impose a strong inductive bias similarly to using convolution for images.
So a model operating on neural graphs, such as a graph neural network (GNN) and our NiNo model, can be used in diverse tasks and should be able to learn parameter prediction rules that generalize better with fewer samples than, for example, MLPs. However, to fully leverage the neural graphs in practice, we need to accurately construct them, which is not trivial for such networks as transformers, motivating us in this work.


